Some of the radiation incidents on the PV solar cells are reflected from the PV module. Another percentage of the incident radiation is stored in the PV module as heat; this amount of heat causes raising in the surface temperature of the PV module. The ratio between the PV module’s electrical power and the solar radiation incident on the PV module is called the electrical efficiency of the PV module.1ηPVmodule=TheelectricalpowerproducedfromthePVmoduleSolarradiationincidentonthePVmodule\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
